I have never used Gravity Flux in a serious EQ matter.  I have used it in the following places.<br>
<br>
North Ro - Gravity Fluxing Dorn for revenge.  Always a goodie.<br>
Arena - Gravity flux your friends.  Weee...like being in Sebilis.<br>
City of Mist - Bouncing Wizards to get the BrainBite Mob.<br>
Rathe Mountains - Got to love Gravity Fluxing Giants.<br>
Great Divide - Shardwurms see commentary on Giants.<br>
<br>
Another part of Gravity Flux is that it takes a lot of mana for 300 damage.  You wont kill anything with it before you run out of mana.<br>
<br>
For Charm Soloing, go to the Warrens and get yourself a bag of dice to hand to Miranda in Stonebrunt Mountains for a Ball of Twine, its a 4 shot snare item.<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Level 62 Chanter - Epic Heroes - Vazelle<br>
